a fatal crash involving a tesla cybertruck occurred early wednesday in piedmont california resulting in three deaths and one serious injury the accident happened around 308 am when the cybertruck mounted a curb struck a cement wall and became wedged between the wall and a tree the front of the vehicle caught fire

the cybertrucks automated emergency alert system notified authorities immediately after the crash three occupants were pronounced dead at the scene while a passerby rescued a fourth person who was hospitalized with severe injuries investigators suspect speed may have been a factor but the involvement of drugs or alcohol has not been ruled out

this tragic event highlights concerns about vehicle safety and comes as teslas cybertruck which has been on the market for about a year faces scrutiny following multiple recalls the investigation into the crash is ongoing
